    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-03T23:53:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-31T03:30:00-05:00" n="543"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Korea)/9–446: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Political Adviser in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Langdon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-09-04T13:53:00+09:00"
                            notBefore="1946-08-31T17:30:00+09:00">undated</date>.<lb/>[Received
                        September 4—1:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tfpol 30 [to Tokyo]. 103. Timing and text of Under Secretary’s statement
                    following immediately upon General Hodge’s statement <pb facs="0747" n="735"
                        xml:id="pg_735"/> here<note n="46" xml:id="d543fn1">The text of General
                        Hodge’s statement was transmitted by telegram on August 31 from Seoul;
                        received at 5:30 p.m.</note> was eminently effective. All Korean papers from
                    extreme Eight to extreme Left and Korean news services carried full layout
                        <gloss target="#t_UP1">UP</gloss> Washington coverage and enthusiastically
                    received by Korean people. Such frank and definitive statement of policy at
                    State <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> level believed to be of great
                    assistance stabilizing and crystallizing future Korean political activities.
                    High level emphasis to previous statements by Hodge most helpful. Further,
                    statement gave army personnel here boost in appreciation of occupational tasks.
                    Hodge grateful for assistance and hopes in future <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> will issue similar statements of high level policy as need
                    develops.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Langdon</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
